From: Ayush <ayushverma567@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Apr 2026 14:25:20 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] feat(brand): integrate Fintrest identity at the chrome layer
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Lays the design-system foundation (tokens, Aperture mark, type) and
swaps the emoji logos + softens the chat intro, without touching any
of the working trading panes.

New
- frontend/src/tokens.js — source of truth for colors, spacing, radii,
  typography, motion. All future UI work should consume these.
- frontend/src/Aperture.jsx — reusable React component of the Fintrest
  mark with solid/outline/glyph variants.
- frontend/public/favicon.svg — V2 outlined aperture on Carbon.
- frontend/public/landing.html — self-contained marketing page served
  at /landing.html. Hero, triad, editorial quote, waitlist form.
- fintrest-*.md / .svg — brand + product + build + copy + landing specs.

Changed
- frontend/src/App.js — imports Aperture, replaces the two 💹 emoji
  logos (auth modal + header) with the mark, softens the chat intro
  to match the Fintrest voice ("tell you what the numbers actually
  say" rather than "AI-powered financial advisor"). Trading panes
  untouched.
- frontend/src/index.css — Fintrest globals (Carbon/Pearl, Inter +
  Fraunces + JetBrains Mono, focus rings, reduced-motion). Preserves
  the upstream .chart-tv-badge styles.
- frontend/public/index.html — real title/description/OG tags, theme
  color #0A0B0C, Google Fonts wired up, new favicon link.
- frontend/public/manifest.json — Fintrest name, theme/background
  #0A0B0C.

Deliberately out of scope
- The yellow #f7c843 accent inside watchlist/chart/compare panes.
  It's load-bearing at 20+ sites with no tests; migrating it needs
  its own pass with smoke tests.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
